Paper: hep-th/9502013

Date: 1995-02-02

Title: Remarks on Non-Abelian Duality in N=1 Supersymmetric Gauge Theories

Comments: 17 pages, harvmac

Journal-ref: Phys. Lett. B351 (1995) 220

Recently Seiberg has conjectured a duality symmetry connecting differenttheories of the supersymmetric QCD type. We provide support for this conjectureby analyzing a flat direction of the theory along which the two dual theoriesgo over to the same theory in the IR.